// TLCS Main Indicator — Changelog
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// v2.4.2  (2026-05-31)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// FIX: Break-Even SL no longer silently disabled in trail-only (single-lot) mode.
//
// ROOT CAUSE:
//   A conditional block was automatically setting breakEvenEnabled = false
//   whenever all TP profit ratios (TP2, TP3, TP4) were 0. Since trail-only
//   mode sets all ratios to 0, break-even was never firing — meaning the SL
//   never moved to entry after TP1 was hit.
//
// CHANGE (in the Calculations section, just before varip Settings settings):
//
//   BEFORE (v2.4.1 — BROKEN):
//   ─────────────────────────
//   var breakEvenEnabled = breakEvenEnabledInput
//   if tp2ProfitRatioInput == 0 and tp3ProfitRatioInput == 0 and tp4ProfitRatioInput == 0
//       breakEvenEnabled := false          // ← Silently killed Break Even in trail-only mode!
//
//   AFTER (v2.4.2 — FIXED):
//   ────────────────────────
//   var breakEvenEnabled = breakEvenEnabledInput
//   // Break Even is now controlled purely by the user's "Break Even" toggle in settings.
//   // It correctly fires in BOTH trail-only mode (ratios = 0) AND multi-lot mode (ratios > 0).
//   // → TP1 hit: SL moves to Entry (Break Even)
//   // → TP2 hit: SL moves to TP1
//   // → TP3 hit: SL moves to TP2
//
// EFFECT:
//   On a SHORT trade with entry 3.322 and SL at 3.357:
//     • TP1 (3.275) hit  → SL now correctly steps down to 3.322 (entry / break-even)
//     • Trailing SL then continues to track price after TP1 milestone
//   Works identically for LONG trades (SL steps up to entry after TP1 hit).
//
// v2.4.1  (2026-05-30)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// FEAT: Universal TP Ratio Engine
//   Auto-normalizes TP ratios so their sum is capped at 99%, ensuring the
//   trailing SL always has an open position to protect regardless of lot mode.
//   Single-lot mode (all = 0): TPs fire as milestone triggers only.
//   Multi-lot mode (values > 0): TPs close partial lots, residual trails.
//
// v2.4.0  (2026-05-29)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// FEAT: Hybrid Trailing SL architecture
//   TP1 acts as milestone trigger to activate trailing stop.
//   session.trailingSLActivated + session.trailingSLLevel fields added to
//   TradeLogic type. Trail fires on triggerTrailingSL condition after TP1 hit.
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
